HEADWORD: Matelotte
<hw>Mat"e*lotte</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧t"⟦esl⟧*l⟦ocr⟧t)</pr> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>matelote</ets>, fr. <ets>matelot</ets> a
sailor; properly, a dish such as a sailors prepare.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A stew, commonly of fish, flavored with wine, and served with a
wine sauce containing onions, mushrooms, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An old dance of sailors, in double time, and
somewhat like a hornpipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mateology</ent>⟦br⟧
